The paper deals with information theoretic security, resolvability, and channel synthesis, which are all topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses lossy source coding, which falls under the category of compression and coding (cs.CR). The use of random codebooks and probability analysis suggests a connection to stochastic processes and their applications (cs.SI). The paper also involves analyzing the decay rate of certain quantities, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on achieving certain phenomena with high probability suggests a connection to probabilistic methods and randomized algorithms (cs.LG).
